title: DSC 209R Project 2: Deceptive Visualization
description: This was my second project for DSC209R. It involved creating an Earnest and Deceptive visualization. I chose to use traffic stop data for the city of San Diego.

title: DSC 209R Project 1: Expository Visualization
description: This was my first project for DSC 209R, which involved designing a single static visualization to effectively communicate an idea about climate data in major US Cities.

title: DSC 207R Final Project: Machine Learning on NHL Hockey Data
description: Research Questions: a) Can we identify features that are correlated with game outcome (win/loss) at the player or team level? b) Can we use an ML Regression model to predict goals scored in a season based on goals scored by players in their previous 2 seasons? and c) Can we use an ML Classification model to predict wins and losses?
